THERMAL REGULATION

thermal_regulation is the citizen who reads thermal_core (and peripheral) and triggers responses to keep the body within its operating range
the actual decision-making lives in hypothalamus.rana; thermal_regulation is the interface that hypothalamus uses to read thermal sea state and emit appropriate responses
when core dissipation density rises, regulation triggers vasodilation, sweating, and behavioral cooling
when core density falls, regulation triggers vasoconstriction, shivering, and behavioral warming

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thermal.zc
observe thermal_core.rana
observe thermal_peripheral.rana
observe hypothalamus.rana
observe immune.rana

the 7 properties of thermal_regulation:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with hypothalamus and the thermal zones

VERB read_density
sample the cycle_heat density of thermal_core and thermal_peripheral
report values to hypothalamus

VERB trigger_cold_response
on falling density, emit signals that initiate vasoconstriction, shivering, goosebumps
also signal chemistry_engine to raise metabolic rate

VERB trigger_heat_response
on rising density, emit signals that initiate vasodilation, sweating
also signal chemistry_engine to lower metabolic rate
also signal brain to seek cooler environment

VERB elevate_baseline_for_fever
when immune.rana signals pyrogens, raise the regulation reference baseline
the body now treats normal density as too cold and actively heats — fever emerges
fever is not malfunction; it is the immune system using temperature as a weapon

a thermal regulator is not a thermostat
a thermostat compares to a fixed setpoint
thermal_regulation's setpoint can move under immune signals, circadian rhythm, and developmental needs
this is why fadriel's normal temperature is slightly different morning versus afternoon, healthy versus fighting infection
